Bring a #pot of @water{250%ml} to the boil with the @chicken stock pot{1/2}. Preheat your #oven to 200 degrees.

Once your water is boiling, stir to dissolve your stock pot, then add the @bulgur wheat{100%g}. Stir together, put a lid on the #pot and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{20-25%mins}, or until the rest of the meal is ready. Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and leave for a couple of mins to get hot.

Season each @British chicken breasts{2} with a @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{} and lay them in the #frying pan skin-side down. Cook for ~{5-6%mins} until the skin is golden, then turn over and cook on the flesh side for ~{1%minute more}. Drizzle a little @olive oil{} on a #baking tray{} and then add your chicken to the tray (skin-side up). Put the tray on the top shelf of your #oven for ~{20%mins}, then remove from your oven and leave to rest for ~{5%mins}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Don't wash up your frying pan - you'll use it later!

While your bulgur wheat and chicken are cooking, tackle the veg! Chop off the root and the green leafy part from the @leek{1}, then cut the leek in half lengthways. Thinly slice into half moon shapes. Trim both ends off the @courgette{1} and cut into slices about ½cm wide. Pull the @basil{1} leaves off their stalks. Finely chop the basil stalks. Finely chop half the basil leaves and roughly chop the other half (keep these basil parts separate).

Mix your finely chopped basil leaves with the @extra virgin olive oil{2%tbsp}, along with a @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. This is your basil oil!

Put the @unsalted butter{30%g} in the #frying pan you cooked the chicken, and put it on medium heat. Once melted, add your leek and basil stalks and cook for ~{3%mins} before adding your courgette. Add a @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{} and cook together on low heat for ~{8%mins}, stirring occasionally, until soft.

When the 8 mins are up, remove the #pan from the heat and add your roughly chopped basil leaves. Crumble in the @feta cheese{1%100g block} and gently stir through your veggies. When your bulgur wheat is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork. Taste and add more salt and black pepper if you feel it needs it.

Once your chicken is cooked and rested, put it on a #chopping board{} and cut it into slices about 1cm wide.

Serve your bulgur wheat in large #bowls{} with your buttery veggies, chicken and your basil oil drizzled over. Enjoy!